  "time_ut": 1656482283,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0dd6\u0dbd\u0dd2 10 \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dcf \u0daf\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dcf \u0dbb\u0da7 \u0d85\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db8\u0dab\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Paralyzing the country until July 10",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Our country, nicknamed the pearl of the Indian Ocean, is facing a very sad fate. Mother or daughter in line for gas. Dad is in the fuel line. The son is in the passport queue. The people of Buruthu are ready to leave the country. That's how much the country has become bitter for the people of the country. It is almost impossible to recognize what kind of curse or sin this is.",
        "After the last drop of oil has sat, the ministers go to countries in search of oil. Going to find oil at the last moment. It is not difficult to calculate whether the amount of oil received is enough for a few days. But there is no such calculation. People suffer in fuel queues for weeks. Minister Bandula Gunawardena stated that fuel will be released only for essential services from yesterday. It is valid until the 10th. Accordingly, fuel is released only for health, defense, power, export industries etc.",
        "Petroleum and Energy Minister Kanchana Wijesekera said while holding a press conference that an oil tanker is on its way. But in the end it was reported that the ship passed our country. The minister stated that the ship left because there were no dollars. The minister also said that no country will lend oil to our country. The depth of the statement that our country has made is very clear. No one has the right to drag a country to such a shameful and tragic fate.",
        "Although Minister Bandula Gunawardena said that fuel will be provided only for essential services, it is a question whether the fuel is at a sufficient level for that. Doctors, nurses and health staff members do not have time to treat patients. Instead, they have to wait in fuel queues. Hospitals are starting to close due to insufficient staff. This is a very dangerous situation.",
        "The Association of Government Medical Officers says that people should be very careful during this period due to shortage of medicines and transportation difficulties. The Association of Government Medical Officers has also emphasized that if there is an accident at work, at home, it is difficult to provide transport facilities to the patient, as well as to provide transport facilities to doctors and other hospital staff.",
        "A lot of insecurity has been created on all sides. National security is not only saving the country from terrorists and invaders. Ensuring the safety of all citizens living in that country is within the scope of national security. But that protection has been lost today. It should be emphasized here that what is a regime that cannot protect the citizen.",
        "It has been announced that we can get fuel from Russia at a lower price than the current price. When the leaders of parties independent from the government met the Russian ambassador in this country, he said that the President of Sri Lanka should call the Russian President on the phone and ask for what is needed.",
        "The fate of the country's poor children's education is a cause for concern for the country's future. Education is the most precious wealth of unborn poor children. Our sons and daughters are deprived of that education today. And malnutrition has become a legacy. A human disaster is no stranger than this. The country that has become the model of all perversions has become the latest example of human disaster.",
        "It is hard to imagine why the crisis has been waiting to escalate to such an extent. It has been proved that a country cannot be built by the fairy tales of the politicians and the arrogant and arrogant people. Rescuing people from this misery should be made the top priority."
      ],
